// src/pages/Privacy.js
import React from 'react';
import { Container, Box, Typography, Link as MuiLink } from '@mui/material';

const Privacy = () => (
  <Container sx={{ py: 4 }}>
    <Box>
      <Typography variant="h4" gutterBottom>
        Privacy Policy
      </Typography>
      <Typography paragraph>
        LincolnVerse (“we”, “us”, “our”) is committed to protecting your privacy.
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>
        1. Information We Collect
      </Typography>
      <Typography paragraph>
        We collect data you provide (e.g., username, email) and usage data (searches, saved items).
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>
        2. How We Use Your Information
      </Typography>
      <Typography paragraph>
        To authenticate you, improve our service, and communicate updates.
      </Typography>
      <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>
        3. Third-Party Services
      </Typography>
      <Typography paragraph>
        We use the Openverse API for media search. Please review their own data practices.
      </Typography>
      <Typography paragraph>
        If you have questions, contact us at{' '}
        <MuiLink href="mailto:support@lincolnverse.com">support@lincolnverse.com</MuiLink>.
      </Typography>
    </Box>
  </Container>
);

export default Privacy;
